<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1633">
Your task is to count the number of ways to construct sum $n$ by throwing a dice one or more times. Each throw produces an outcome between $1$ and  $6$.<br />
<br />
For example, if $n=3$, there are $4$ ways:<ul>
<li> $1+1+1$<br />
<li> $1+2$<br />
<li> $2+1$<br />
<li> $3$<br />
</ul>
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line has an integer $n$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print the number of ways modulo $10^9+7$.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 10^6$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>3</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>4</code>    </div>
